snippet.textDisplay:
I don’t understand Canada’s logic.
Here is an example following that logic: If you have 10 hens, and one of them had sneaked out to your neighbour’s yard for a day or two and when it came back, you realized it was showing symptoms of illness. Your neighbour then tells you his hens are sick and he has quarantined the sick ones IN HIS OWN YARD. So the logical thing would be for you to put that hen of yours in quarantine until you get her tested. But the current Canadian logical thing to do would be to put that hen back with it’s family because it’s a hen too. We get that it’s a hen too but you are risking infecting all other hens. If your neighbor had quarantined his OWN infected hens, then why wouldn’t you quarantine your infected hen too? Are you trying to get your other hens to die?!!!
